item.title: Medal of Honor 11-minute multiplayer video
item.dc:creator: eternalness
item.description:
CTID:

That, but then neither is the Frostbite engine, really. It’s been around for a good 3-4 years too. The Frostbite 2 engine is next-gen, but as far as I’m aware the only game that’s using it is Battlefield 3.

There are multiple versions of Frostbite. Bad Company 1 ran on the Frostbite 1.0 and Bad Company 2 and Battlefield 1943 run on Frostbite 1.5. I agree that Frostbite 1.0 is no longer a next gen engine, but Frostbite 1.5, albeit still quite similar to 1.0, does support alot more next gen features like DX11 and tactical destruction 2.0 compared to Unreal 3. Unreal 3 does have some destruction, buts its done by PhysX which is the worst possible physics engine because its a proprietary engine which alienates all ATi users even though their cards are very capable of running it.

item.title: Medal of Honor 11-minute multiplayer video
item.dc:creator: CTID
item.description:
Bad Company 2’s animations are fucking awesome, imo. They seriously actually have separate animations running down hills and up them, etc. Most games just use the same running animation for everything and hope no one notices. In Bad Company 2, if you watch some one running down a hill, you can actually see the character shift his weight back while he’s running, making it seem like “Well, I’ll lean backward while I run so that I don’t lose my balance and fall.”

Anyone know if Medal of Honor’s MP has vehicles? I didn’t watch the video if it showed.
